.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Closes an outbound half of the channel.
When the peer receives all the messages sent prior to the calling
\f[B]chdone\f[] all its subsequent attempts to receive will fail with
\f[B]EPIPE\f[] error.
.PP
\f[B]ch\f[]: The channel.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
